Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Shawn P. Ahrens in court with attorney Thomas L. Steinman.  Defendant Shawn P. Ahrens in custody.  Sue Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  No Contest Plea entered, advised of constitutional rights, plea accepted by Court.  Court finds Def. guilty.  Court imposes sentence.

Defendant Shawn P. Ahrens in court with attorney Thomas L. Steinman.  Defendant Shawn P. Ahrens in custody.  Michael X. Albrecht appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court states case and parties state appearances.  Atty Steinman requests the Court allow him to waive the time limits for the preliminary hearing.  Court accepts time limit waiver and sets matter for PTC and RD.  Atty Steinman addresses bond condition of no contact w/E.C. (DE's sister).  Requests that be dropped as a condition only while the DE is in custody.  State is in agreement.  Court so orders bond amended to allow contact w/E.C. while DE is in custody only.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for January 9, 2015 at 09:00 am.  Return date scheduled for January 21, 2015 at 01:00 pm.
